<span id="freeTextContainer13904244562692838664">This novel is written for the mature audience. I would introduce this to students in their teen years, once they understand more about the GLBTQ community. This is a great novel because it has short stories within it that address homosexuality. Some of the stories are written by teens who have &quot;come out&quot; or falling in love with those of them same sex as them. Other stories are written by friends and family who have someone in their lives that depicts themselves as GLBT or Q. This novel was well </span>
  <span id="freeText13904244562692838664" style="display:none">This novel is written for the mature audience. I would introduce this to students in their teen years, once they understand more about the GLBTQ community. This is a great novel because it has short stories within it that address homosexuality. Some of the stories are written by teens who have "come out" or falling in love with those of them same sex as them. Other stories are written by friends and family who have someone in their lives that depicts themselves as GLBT or Q. This novel was well written and allows the reader to understand the idea that they are not alone. I felt feelings of hope and perseverance in the writer's stories. </span>
