<div id="review_10343223" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/10343223" />
    <a title="Kricket" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/125201-kricket"><img alt="Kricket" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1455408697p2/125201.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/10343223?book_show_action=true">Dec 12, 2007</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kricket" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kricket" href="/user/show/125201-kricket">Kricket</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=2005-and-earlier">2005-and-earlier</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=2011">2011</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=lgbtq">lgbtq</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=teen-fiction">teen-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=short-stories">short-stories</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/125201-kricket?shelf=who-am-i">who-am-i</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer10343223" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4571084374180289195">reading this for the second time. i got it from the public library when i was in high school. i thought the stories were about depression. instead it became the first piece(s) of gltbq teen fiction i ever read. in light of current events in my hometown, i&apos;m amazed our library even owned this book back in 1998 or whatever. i wish i knew who the teen librarian back then was so i could track her down and hug her. (note to self: do this.)<br/><br/>ANYWAY. this is a terrific selection of stories that holds up </span>
  <span id="freeText4571084374180289195" style="display:none">reading this for the second time. i got it from the public library when i was in high school. i thought the stories were about depression. instead it became the first piece(s) of gltbq teen fiction i ever read. in light of current events in my hometown, i'm amazed our library even owned this book back in 1998 or whatever. i wish i knew who the teen librarian back then was so i could track her down and hug her. (note to self: do this.)<br /><br />ANYWAY. this is a terrific selection of stories that holds up pretty well for having been published in 1994. some of them i immediately remembered upon beginning them ('three mondays in july' by giblin, 'parents' night' by nancy garden, 'supper' by newman, and 'dancing backwards' by bauer). others i'm fairly sure i skipped the first time around ('blood sister' by yolen and 'in the tunnels' by sleator.) i skimmed them this time. still didn't like them that much. oh and fun fact: gregory maguire of 'wicked' fame has a really great story in here.<br /><br />the packaging, alas, is pretty dated. i was the first person to check out the book in quite some time. maybe time to put out a new edition? all in all, really good stuff and great fun to re-read.</span>
  <a data-text-id="4571084374180289195" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


