  <div class="friendReviews elementListBrown" >
    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_47598082" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/47598082" />
    <a title="Jennifer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/1763804-jennifer"><img alt="Jennifer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1491327883p2/1763804.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/47598082?book_show_action=true">Feb 26, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jennifer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jennifer" href="/user/show/1763804-jennifer">Jennifer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer47598082" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer10209776139253197282">This is a reread, but a reread from so long ago that I barely remember most of the stories, and I know there are several I didn&apos;t read at all. It&apos;s an interesting collection of coming out stories and other stories about growing up and dealing with gay identity. As with any anthology, the quality is mixed, but no story in here is actively <i>bad</i>. My personal favorite story is Francesca Lia Block&apos;s lyrical &quot;Winnie and Tommy,&quot; but there are many gems. If the subject matter is something you&apos;re interest</span>
  <span id="freeText10209776139253197282" style="display:none">This is a reread, but a reread from so long ago that I barely remember most of the stories, and I know there are several I didn't read at all. It's an interesting collection of coming out stories and other stories about growing up and dealing with gay identity. As with any anthology, the quality is mixed, but no story in here is actively <i>bad</i>. My personal favorite story is Francesca Lia Block's lyrical "Winnie and Tommy," but there are many gems. If the subject matter is something you're interested in, I highly recommend it.<br /><br />One note, though: this was published in 1994, and it's definitely a product of its time. If you aren't interested in gay literature where the specter of AIDS looms large, you may want to avoid some of the stories.</span>
  <a data-text-id="10209776139253197282" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

